                'key' => 'history-of-aizawl-diocese',
                'name' => 'History of Aizawl Diocese',
                'description' => 'The Diocese of Aizawl was formerly known as the Diocese of Silchar. The Diocese of Silchar was made up of the districts of Cachar Hailakandi and Karimganj of Assam State, the entire Tripura and Mizoram States.The Diocese is bounded on the west by Bangladesh while the northern extremity wedges into the segment of a circle which touches from the East Khasi Hills of Meghalaya to the North Cachar Hills of Assam, on the northern section of  he east lies Manipur state, on the southern section the Chin Hills of Myanmar, on the south, the northern extremity of Arakan districts of Myanmar.',
                'value' => '<p>The Diocese of Aizawl was formerly known as the Diocese of Silchar. The Diocese of Silchar was made up of the districts of Cachar Hailakandi and Karimganj of Assam State, the entire Tripura and Mizoram States.The Diocese is bounded on the west by Bangladesh while the northern extremity wedges into the segment of a circle which touches from the East Khasi Hills of Meghalaya to the North Cachar Hills of Assam, on the northern section of he east lies Manipur state, on the southern section the Chin Hills of Myanmar, on the south, the&nbsp;northern extremity of Arakan districts of Myanmar.<br><br>This ecclesiastical unit was established as the Prefecture Apostolic of Haflong by an Apostolic Brief &ldquo;Fit Numquam&rdquo; dated January 17,1952, and entrusted to the Holy Cross Fathers of the Canadian Province. By an Apostolic construction of Pope Paul VI &lsquo;Omnium Sohcitudo&rsquo;, dated June 26, 1969, the Prefecture of Haflong was raised to the status of a Diocese with the Episcopal See at Silchar. Most Rev Denzil D&rsquo;Souza became the first Bishop of the Diocese of Silchar. In December 1983, the northern Cachar Hills district was detached from the Diocese of Silchar and joined to the new Diocese of Diphu.</p>
                            <p>On 7th February 1996 the entire State of Tripura was cut off from the Diocese of Silchar thereby forming the New Diocese of Agartala, of which Rev Fr Lumen Monteiro CSC, was appointed as its first Bishop. The remaining portion of Silchar Diocese comprises at present the districts of Cachar, Hailakandi and Karimganj (Barrak Valley) of Assam State and the entire State of Mizoram.&nbsp; By the division of Silchar Diocese on 7th February 1996, it is henceforth to be called Aizawl Diocese, and its Episcopal See is transferred from Silchar to Aizawl.<br><br>Due to Bishop Denzil&rsquo;s ill-health, on his resignation, Rt Rev. Lumen Monteiro, CSC was appointed the Apostolic Administrator of Aizawl Diocese. Bishop Denzil D&rsquo;Souza went to eternal reward on the 25th Oct 2002. The new Bishop-elect, Fr. Stephen Roltuanga, CSC, was ordained Bishop on the 2nd February, 2002. Fr. Joachim Walder was ordained Auxiliary Bishop of Aizawl on 28 th May 2023.</p>
                            <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>HISTORY OF CATHOLIC CHURCH IN MIZORAM</strong><br>Mizorama Catholic Kohhran lo indin chhoh d&acirc;n</p>
                            <p style="text-align: left;">Kum 1922-ah Shillonga traininga kal, Pu Aichh&ucirc;nga, Agriculture Demonstrator chuan Catholic rinna chungch&acirc;ng ziahna lehkha thenkhat a rawn h&acirc;wn a. Ch&ucirc;ng lehkhate an lo chhiar atangin mi thenkhatten Catholic rinna chu pawmin, February ni 1, 1925-ah mi 5, Lianchheua, Thangphunga, L&ecirc;nga, Chalchhuna leh Lalb&acirc;na te, Tl&acirc;ngnuam mi vekten Catholic Kohhran an din ta a. Thangphunga chu Leader-ah an hmang a, Tl&acirc;ngnuama L&ecirc;nga inah an inkh&acirc;wm thin a. Hetia Kohhran an din hnu hian Laldailova te nupa te, Dr. Lalhuta, Chawnga leh Hr&acirc;ngnghilhlova ten an rawn zawm leh a. Mumal taka Catholic Kohhran hi din ngheh a nih theih n&acirc;n Chittagonga awm, Rev. Fr. Phileas Boulay an zuk d&acirc;wr hnuin, a hun remch&acirc;ng hmasa berah Father chu Mizoramah rawn kalin, November ni 28,1925-ah Aiz&acirc;wl a rawn thleng a. Aizawla ni 8 a ch&acirc;m chh&ucirc;ngin Pu Thangphunga fapa Joseph Francis Laldailova leh Pu L&ecirc;nga fanu Mary Teresa Lalbiakthangi te chu December ni 6, 1925-ah baptisma chantirir, Chittagong lamah a hawsan leh ta rih a.<br><br>Kum 1926 kum tir lamah chuan Kohhran member 200 lai an tling chho ta a. Kohhran enkawltu t&ucirc;r catechist neih t&ucirc;la an hriat av&acirc;ngin Chittagonga awm Rev. Fr. Boulay d&acirc;wr t&ucirc;rin May ni 13, 1926-ah Thangphunga, Bula, Chawnga, Chalchhuna leh Lalt&ucirc;ra te chu Chittagong-ah kalin Father an zuk d&acirc;wr a, ani chuan anni chu catechist at&acirc;n a lo ruat zui a, Secretary-ah Thangphunga a ruat a. Kal t&ucirc;ra ruat zinga mi Lianchheuva chu a kal ve thei ta lo va, mahse Father hian catechist-ah a ruat tel ta tho a ni. Kum 1927 January ni 10-ah t&ucirc;na Christ the King Cathedral dinna hmunah hian biak in hmun t&ucirc;r laih z&acirc;wl hna an tan a. Manipur Pherz&acirc;wl khua atanga Catholic Kohhran chanchin hriat chian tuma lo kal, Hr&acirc;ngliana leh Zaneihthanga te pahnih chu Mathew Laldailovan ama sumin biak in hmun lai t&ucirc;r hian a lo ruai a. Biak in hi r&acirc;p ina sak a ni a, February thlaah sa zovin an luah zui ngh&acirc;l a. Biak in hi Christ the King Church tih a ni.<br><br>Kum 1929 August ni 20-ah mi 6-in Badarpur tlawhin, Vicar General Rev. Fr. Boulay chuan baptisma a lo chantir a, chung mite chu Peter Thangphunga, John Chawnga, Jacob M&acirc;nga, Paul Bula, Phillip Lianng&ucirc;ra leh Joseph Saitul&ecirc;ra te an ni. Kum 1930 October ni 12-ah Fr. Boulay hian Francis Thans&acirc;nga leh Anthony Chalthangvunga te baptisma a chantir bawk. Mizorama Catholic mite harsatna hriain, Rev. Fr. Boulay thl&acirc;ktu Rev. Fr. L.Coggin chuan Kohhran hruaitute hn&ecirc;nah thi mai t&ucirc;rte baptisma chantir theihna thuneihna a pe a ni.<br><br>Mizorama Kohhran lo ding hmasaten Catholic Kohhran din ngheh a nih loh n&acirc;n nasa takin an dod&acirc;l a, chumi av&acirc;ng chuan rawn thutchilh t&ucirc;rin Catholic Puithiamte an rawn l&ucirc;t mai thei lo va, kum 10 liam hnu kum 1935-ah Rev. Fr. L. Goggin CSC chu a rawn kal ve leh zawk a. Ch&acirc;m rei lovin a haw leh thuai a. Chittagong Bishop-in Mizorama Catholic Kohhran dinhmun en chiang t&ucirc;rin Rev. Fr. A. Montegny CSC leh Rev. Fr. Robert Lavoie CSC te a rawn tir a, January ni 14, 1946-ah Aiz&acirc;wl rawn l&ucirc;tin, chawlhk&acirc;r khat an ch&acirc;m hnuah January ni 22, 1946-ah an haw leh a. Hemi kum December thlaah Catholic Puithiamte rawn luh phalna Assam Governor office atangin hmuh a ni ta hlauh a. Chumi bawhzui chuan April ni 15, 1947-ah Rev. Fr. George Breen CSC leh Bro. Gilbert Boucher CSC te chu Mizoram thutchilh tawh t&ucirc;rin an lo kal a. An thuthmun at&acirc;n Kulikawn an hmang a, Mizoram pumpui an enkawl a. Mizoram pumpui chu Christ the King Parish bial chh&ucirc;nga awm tihna a ni. Mizoram chu Kohhran mission field ang a nih rih av&acirc;ngin t&ucirc;nhnua Parish enkawltu t&ucirc;r Puithiamte official installation ang hi a awm hran lo. Puithiamte chuan Mizoram khaw hrang hranga Catholic rinna vuantu lo awm tawhte kan kualin hma an la a. Ringtu an lo puang chho ve z&ecirc;l a, khaw 57 laiah Catholic rinna vuantu a awm thei ta hial a ni.</p>
                            <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>PARISH DIN TAN DAN</strong></p>
                            <p style="text-align: left;">Kum 1951 June thlaah Chhingchhipah Puithiam thuthmun siam a ni a, Chhingchhip Parish hawng zuiin, St. Peter the Apostle Parish tih a ni zui a. Kum 1953 October thlaah Kolasib Parish hawngin, St. Joseph the Worker Parish tih a ni a. Christ the King Parish hi Aiz&acirc;wl Parish tite pawhin sawi a ni bawk. Kum 1966 ram buai hmain Mizoramah Parish pathum a ding hman chauh a ni. H&ecirc;ng Parish pathumte atang hian a hnuah Parish thar indang an lo awm chho ve z&ecirc;l a, Christ the King Parish atang hian kum 1993-ah St. Mary&rsquo;s Parish, Electric V&ecirc;ng te, kum 1999-ah St. Paul the Apostle Parish, Sihphir leh kum 2011-ah Mary Mother of Compassion Parish, Sate&ecirc;k te an indang leh a ni. Kum 1947-a Puithiam thutchilh kan lo nih atanga kum 75 a han liam meuh chuan Mizoram chh&ucirc;ngah Parish 24 lai kan lo nei ta a, a l&acirc;wmawm hle mai. <br><br>Kum 1996 February ni 7-ah Bishop thuthmun chu Silchar atangin Aiz&acirc;wlah sawn a ni a, Silchar Diocese tih thin chu Aizawl Diocese tih a lo ni ta a, hemi rual hian Christ the King Parish pawh Christ the King Cathedral Parish tih a ni zui ta a ni.</p>',
